es-mad-men-kardashians-lots-more/65626 |archivedate=October 5, 2010 }}</ref>\n |ShortSummary = The one-hour premiere episode introduces viewers to Kody Brown, his three wives Meri, Janelle and Christine, and their twelve children. They live in a ranch-style home that, although interconnected, is subdivided into three separate apartments that give each wife her own bedroom, kitchen and living space.<ref name=\"Stuever\">{{Cite news |last=Stuever |first=Hank |title=TLC's 'Sister Wives': Frank, entertaining TV about polygamist Browns in Utah |work=[[The Washington Post]] |date=September 25, 2010 |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2010/09/23/AR2010092304939.html |accessdate=October 30, 2010}}</ref><ref name=\"Perigard\">{{Cite news |last=Perigard |first=Mark A. |title=It's all four one, one four all in TLC's 'Sister Wives' |date=September 26, 2010 |work=[[Boston Herald]] |url=http://www.bostonherald.com/entertainment/television/reviews/view/20100925its_all_four_one_one_four_all_in_tlcs_sister_wives/srvc=home&position=7 |accessdate=October 30, 2010}}</ref> Eventually, Kody and his wives tell the children he is courting a fourth wife, Robyn Sullivan, who herself already has three children.<ref name=\"Perigard\" /><ref>{{Cite news |last=Fralic |first=Shelley |title=Sister Wives and the puzzle of polygamy |work=[[The Vancouver Sun]] |date=September 26, 2010 |url=http://communities.canada.com/vancouversun/print.aspx?postid=697951 |accessdate=October 30, 2010 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101009172424/http://communities.canada.com/vancouversun/print.aspx?postid=697951 |archivedate=October 9, 2010 }}</ref> Meanwhile, the wives explain they do not plan to force their children into polygamist lifestyles or arrange their marriages for them, but rather will encourage them to make their own choices.<ref name=\"Stuever\" /><ref name=\"Oh\">{{Cite news |last=Oh |first=Eunice |title=Polygamist Stars of ''Sister Wives'' Hope to Raise 'Moral and Ethical' Children |date=September 24, 2010 |work=[[People (magazine)|People]] |url=http://www.people.com/people/article/0,,20428355,00.html |accessdate=October 30, 2010}}</ref> The children attend a polygamist cooperative school, while Kody and Janelle both work full-time as Meri pursues a long-delayed college degree.<ref name=\"Stuever\" /> The family discusses their strong spiritual faith, and the episode includes both blessings at dinner and an evening family prayer.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Tenety |first=Elizabeth |title='Sister Wives': polygamy 'comes out' on TLC |work=[[Washington Post]] |date=September 26, 2010 |url=http://onfaith.washingtonpost.com/onfaith/undergod/2010/09/sister_wives_polygamy_comes_to_tlc.html |accessdate=October 30, 2010}}</ref> The episode also highlights the fact that Brown operates on a rotating schedule that dictates which wife he will spend the night with. Although Brown has sex with all three of his wives, they make clear the women never sleep with each other, a concept they consider immoral.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Katz |first=Neil |title=Sister Wives (PICTURE): Could You Survive a Polygamous Marriage? |work=[[CBS News]] |date=September 27, 2010 |url=http://www.cbsnews.com/8301-504763_162-20017701-10391704.html |accessdate=October 30, 2010}}</ref> The episode ends with Kody going on a date with Robyn.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Brooks |first=Joanna |title=TLC Premieres Polygamy Reality Show ''Sister Wives'' |date=September 27, 2010 |work=[[Religion Dispatches]] |url=http://www.religiondispatches.org/dispatches/joannabrooks/3424/tlc_premieres_polygamy_reality_show_sister_wives_/ |accessdate=October 30, 2010}}</ref>\n |LineColor=B30713\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber=2\n |EpisodeNumber2=2\n |Title=Courting a Fourth Wife\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2010|10|03}}\n |Aux4=1.88<ref name=\"Ep2Rate\">{{Cite news|last=Seidman |first=Robert |title=Sunday Cable Ratings: ''Broadwalk Empire'' Mostly Stable; ''Rubicon'' Still Tiny; ''Mad Men'', ''Kardashians'', ''Dexter'' & Lots More |work=TV by the Numbers |date=October 5, 2010 |url=http://tvbythenumbers.com/2010/10/05/sunday-cable-ratings-boardwalk-empire-mostly-stable-rubicon-still-tiny-mad-men-kardashians-dexter-lots-more/66791 |accessdate=October 30, 2010 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101010123912/http://tvbythenumbers.com/2010/10/05/sunday-cable-ratings-boardwalk-empire-mostly-stable-rubicon-still-tiny-mad-men-kardashians-dexter-lots-more/66791 |archivedate=October 10, 2010 }}</ref>\n |ShortSummary = This episode focuses on Kody's dating of Robyn Sullivan, marking the first time he has courted a woman since his third marriage 16 years earlier. Robyn lives five hours away from his home, so Kody must travel far and spend a great amount of time away from the rest of his family to date her. Robyn, who has three children under the age of 10, explains that although she grew up in a polygamist family, she has previously kept the lifestyle a secret until participating on ''Sister Wives''. Meri, who had previously encouraged Kody to marry Janelle and Christine, explains that she met Robyn and encouraged Kody to court her also. Nevertheless, the prospect of a fourth wife requires some adjustment for the three wives, who fear being replaced as companions, as well as for their children, who have grown up with three mothers their entire lives.<ref name=\"Shellnutt\">{{Cite news |last=Shellnutt |first=Kate |title=Sister Wives: Growing pains |work=[[Houston Chronicle]] |date=October 3, 2010 |url=http://blogs.chron.com/tubular/archives/2010/10/sister_wives_gr.html |accessdate=October 30, 2010}}</ref>\n |LineColor=B30713\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber=3\n |EpisodeNumber2=3\n |Title=Wives on the Move\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2010|10|03}}\n |Aux4=2.13<ref name=\"Ep2Rate\" />\n |ShortSummary=Robyn is moving into a new house about a half-mile from the Kody Brown home. Since Kody and Robyn are only engaged, she cannot yet live in the house with the rest of his family. Although ultimately supportive of the idea of the new union, Meri, Janelle and Christine continue to experience conflicted feelings about the change it will bring to the family. Meri experiences an emotional breakdown and talks about the difficulties of being in a polygamist family, and Christine grows particularly upset when she learns Kody sealed his engagement to Robyn with a kiss, since he never kissed the other wives until they were married. Robyn feels remorse for hurting the feelings of the other wives, but expresses happiness and excitement toward joining the family. The whole family helps Robyn load her belongings into the moving truck and bring them to her new home.<ref name=\"Shellnutt\" />\n |LineColor=B30713\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber=4\n |EpisodeNumber2=4\n |Title=Third Wife in Labor\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2010|10|10}}\n |Aux4=1.89<ref name=\"Ep3Rate\">{{Cite news |last=Gorman |first=Bill |title=Sunday Cable Ratings: <nowiki>'</nowiki>''Boardwalk Empire''<nowiki>'</nowiki> Plunges; <nowiki>'</nowiki>''Rubicon''<nowiki>'</nowiki> Up; ''Mad Men'', ''Kardashians'', ''MLB Playoffs'' & More |work=TV by the Numbers |date=October 12, 2010 |url=http://tvbythenumbers.com/2010/10/12/sunday-cable-ratings-boardwalk-empire-plunges-rubicon-up-mad-men-kardashians-mlb-playoffs-more/67765 |accessdate=October 30, 2010}}</ref>\n |ShortSummary=Kody escorts 3rd wife Christine to the hospital for a checkup, since she's slightly past her due date, and they decide to induce labor that day. The hospital staff are very accepting of polygamists and talk casually to Kody and Christine about their family. Although polygamists often give birth at home in the family unit, Christine suffered a miscarriage the previous year and does not want to risk it again.<ref name=\"Shellnutt1010\">{{Cite news |last=Shellnutt |first=Kate |title=Sister Wives: Baby mama drama |date=October 10, 2010 |work=[[Houston Chronicle]] |url=http://blogs.chron.com/tubular/archives/2010/10/sister_wives_ba.html |accessdate=October 30, 2010}}</ref> Robyn takes care of Christine's younger children while she is at the hospital. At one point, Kody stops home and, before returning to the hospital, tries to kiss Robyn off-camera; when the cameras nevertheless capture the moment, Kody admits he did not want to be seen kissing his girlfriend while his wife was in labor. 14-year-old Aspyn, Christine's oldest biological daughter, decides to go with Kody to the hospital to watch the labor.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Deeken |first=Aimee |title=A 13th Child for Kody on 'Sister Wives' |work=[[Weblogs, Inc.#TV Squad|TV Squad]] |url=http://www.tvsquad.com/2010/10/11/a-13th-child-for-kody-on-sister-wives-video/ |accessdate=October 30, 2010}}</ref> Christine gives birth to daughter Truely after a relatively easy labor, and the entire family visits the hospital to see Christine and meet Truely.<ref name=\"Shellnutt1010\" />\n |LineColor=B30713\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber=5\n |EpisodeNumber2=5\n |Title=1st Wife's 20th Anniversary\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2010|10|10}}\n |Aux4=2.05<ref name=\"Ep3Rate\" />\n |ShortSummary=Meri's daughter Mariah tells Kody she wants to study [[pre-medical|pre-med]] at the [[United States Naval Academy|Naval Academy]] in [[Annapolis, Maryland|Annapolis]], [[Maryland]]; Kody is very proud, but fears prejudices against her polygamist family will prevent her from getting in. Later, Kody and Meri go to [[Mexico]] to celebrate their 20th wedding anniversary. Meri discusses her sadness about her infertility problems and the jealousy that has arisen from Kody's recent courtship and engagement to Robyn. When Meri asks how Kody would feel if she had a relationship with another man, he says he finds the idea repulsive, although he admits as a polygamist that his reaction sounds hypocritical. Kody apologizes for his past impatience with Meri's jealousy issues and expresses his love and devotion to her. Later, he proposes having another child through [[in vitro fertilisation]], but she turns down the idea as she is only interested in natural childbirth.<ref name=\"Shellnutt1010\" />\n |LineColor=B30713\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber=6\n |EpisodeNumber2=6\n |Title=A Fourth Wife to Be\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2010|10|17}}\n |Aux4=2.67<ref name=\"Ep4Rate\">{{Cite news|last=Seidman |first=Robert |title=Sunday Cable Ratings: Kardashians Lead; ''Mad Men'' Finale Up; ''Rubicon'' Finale Down; ''Broadway Empire'', ''Sonny with a Chance'' & Much More |work=TV by the Numbers |date=October 19, 2010 |url=http://tvbythenumbers.com/2010/10/19/sunday-cable-ratings-kardarshians-lead-mad-men-finale-up-rubicon-finale-down-boardwalk-empire-sonny-with-a-chance-much-more/68833 |accessdate=October 30, 2010 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101024201649/http://tvbythenumbers.com/2010/10/19/sunday-cable-ratings-kardarshians-lead-mad-men-finale-up-rubicon-finale-down-boardwalk-empire-sonny-with-a-chance-much-more/68833 |archivedate=October 24, 2010 }}</ref>\n |ShortSummary=As Robyn's wedding to Kody approaches, he and the other sister wives clash over whether Robyn is entitled to as much time with Kody as they are: Robyn and Janelle feel as fiancee, she is entitled to equal time with Kody, while Meri and Christine feel she is not until they are married. Despite continued tension over the changes in the family due to the addition of Robyn, the four women mostly get along well. Wanting the others to feel involved, Robyn invites them along to look at dresses, although she doesn't say which dress she's choosing: it's a surprise. Kody joins the women to look at wedding cakes and possible reception locations. During a later interview for the show, Kody reveals he chose the wedding dress himself, which prompts Christine to walk away mid-interview. When she returns, the three wives say they felt betrayed by Kody's actions, but he apologizes and the five reconcile.<ref name=\"Reiher1017\">{{Cite web |last=Reiher |first=Andrea |title='Sister Wives' finale: Will Season 2 see Robyn move into the house? |work=[[Zap2it]] |date=October 17, 2010 |url=http://blog.zap2it.com/frominsidethebox/2010/10/sister-wives-finale-will-season-2-see-robyn-move-into-the-house.html |accessdate=October 30, 2010 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101212055644/http://blog.zap2it.com/frominsidethebox/2010/10/sister-wives-finale-will-season-2-see-robyn-move-into-the-house.html |archivedate=December 12, 2010 }}</ref><ref name=\"Shellnutt1018\">{{Cite news |last=Shellnutt |first=Kate |title=Sister Wives: A polygamist 'coming out' party |date=October 18, 2010 |work=[[Houston Chronicle]] |url=http://blogs.chron.com/tubular/archives/2010/10/sister_wives_a_1.html |accessdate=October 30, 2010}}</ref>\n |LineColor=B30713\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber=7\n |EpisodeNumber2=7\n |Title=Four Wives and Counting...\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2010|10|17}}\n |Aux4 = 2.74<ref name=\"Ep4Rate\" />\n |ShortSummary = The first-season finale episode features the wedding of Kody and Robyn. As the day begins, the family deals with various stresses leading up to the wedding, including the wedding invitations having the wrong address for the ceremony. Robyn struggles to prepare herself while maintaining her hyper and mischievous children. For religious reasons, the cameras are not permitted at the ceremony and it was not televised. During an outdoors reception, Meri, Janelle and Christine present Robyn with a [[Claddagh ring]] to welcome her into the family. As the other wives reflect on their own wedding ceremonies, Janelle, who did not originally come from a polygamist family, reveals she lost most of her family and friends when she married Kody because they were disgusted that she decided to enter into polygamy. As Kody and Robyn prepare to leave for their honeymoon, all four sister wives reflect on how happy they are and how much they look forward to the future.<ref name=\"Reiher1017\" /><ref name=\"Shellnutt1018\" />\n |LineColor=B30713\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber=8\n |EpisodeNumber2=8\n |Title=''Sister Wives'' Special\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2010|10|31}}\n |Aux4=1.82<ref>{{cite web|title=Sunday's Cable Ratings: \"Walking Dead\" Devours the Competition|url=http://thefutoncritic.com/ratings/2010/11/02/sundays-cable-ratings-walking-dead-devours-the-competition-241314/cable_20101031/|work=The Futon Critic|date=November 2, 2010}}</ref>\n |ShortSummary=An hour-long interview hosted by [[NBC]] correspondent [[Natalie Morales (journalist)|Natalie Morales]], who interviews the Brown family about their polygamist lifestyle, new celebrity status and the criminal investigation against them.<ref name=\"Means\" />\n |LineColor=B30713\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber=9\n |EpisodeNumber2=9\n |Title=''Sister Wives'' Honeymoon Special\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2010|11|21}}\n |Aux4=1.82<ref>{{cite web|title=Sunday's Cable Ratings: \"Walking Dead\" Continues to Feast|url=http://thefutoncritic.com/ratings/2010/11/23/sundays-cable-ratings-walking-dead-continues-to-feast-254112/cable_20101121/|work=The Futon Critic|date=November 23, 2010}}</ref>\n |ShortSummary=This episode features Kody and Robyn's 11-day honeymoon in [[San Diego]]. The other three wives continue trying to cope with the addition of a fourth wife, and some feel 11 days was far too long for Kody to be away from the family.<ref name=\"France112asss  meri is cute 0\">{{cite news |last=France |first=Lisa Respers |title=A 'Sister Wives' honeymoon special |publisher=[[CNN]] |date=November 20, 2010 |url=http://marquee.blogs.cnn.com/2010/11/20/a-sister-wives-honeymoon-special/ |accessdate=November 29, 2010}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Gilstrap |first=Peter |title=''Sister Wives Honeymoon Special'': Kody Scores Again! |publisher=[[E!#E! Online|E! Online]] |date=November 22, 2010 |url=http://www.eonline.com/uberblog/the_soup/b212530_sister_wives_honeymoon_special_kody.html |accessdate=November 28, 2010}}</ref> Kody explains the 10-month courtship with Robyn is long for polygamists, for whom courtships usually last up to 90 days, but they feel the extra time has made their relationship stronger. During a trip to the [[San Diego Wild Animal Park]], they point out that many of the animals seem to have polygamist mating relationships.<ref name=\"Reiher1121\">{{cite news |last=Reiher |first=Andrea |title='Sister Wives: Honeymoon Special': The polygamous animal kingdom |publisher=[[Zap2it]] |date=November 21, 2010 |url=http://blog.zap2it.com/frominsidethebox/2010/11/sister-wives-honeymoon-special-the-polygamous-animal-kingdom.html |accessdate=November 28, 2010 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101125090437/http://blog.zap2it.com/frominsidethebox/2010/11/sister-wives-honeymoon-special-the-polygamous-animal-kingdom.html |archive-date=November 25, 2010 |url-status=dead }}</ref> Meanwhile, Meri, Janelle and Christine take the family on a camping trip while Kody and Robyn are away. Robyn insists that Kody frequently call his wives to ensure they remain emotionally connected to him while he is away.<ref>{{cite news |last=Dennis |first=Alicia |title=SNEAK PEEK: ''Sister Wives'' Star Takes Fourth Wife on a Honeymoon |work=[[People (magazine)|People]] |date=November 18, 2010 |url=http://www.people.com/people/article/0,,20443432,00.html |accessdate=November 28, 2010}}</ref> Janelle admits she ignored Kody's calls for the first few days due to her angry feelings about the honeymoon. This special marked the first episode with Robyn featured in the opening credits along with the other wives, and the show's logo was changed to have four gold female rings dangling from a male ring, rather than the original three.<ref name=\"Reiher1121\" />\n |LineColor=B30713\n}}\n}}\n\n=== Season 2 (2011) ===\n{{Episode table |background=#FF69B4 |overall=5 |season=5 |title=30 |airdate=25 |country=US |viewers=10 |episo