f. In the end, the cons out weight the pros.\n|LineColor       = #66DD22\n}}\n{{Episode list\n|EpisodeNumber   = 161\n|EpisodeNumber2  = 9\n|Title           = This Land Is Your Land... Or Hers?\n|OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|3|1}}\n|Viewers         = \n|ShortSummary    = It appears Janelle and Christine will get to build on their preferred lots, but Meri's indecision (or lack of preference) causes hurt feeling for Robyn, who'll get what's left over. \n|LineColor       = #66DD22\n}}\n{{Episode list\n|EpisodeNumber   = 162\n|EpisodeNumber2  = 10\n|Title           = A Breaking Point\n|OriginalAirDate= {{Start date|2020|3|8}}\n|Viewers         = \n|ShortSummary    = Robyn's rental house has been sold and the family must move in less than 60 days. Rentals are scarce. Aurora has a panic attack from the stress.\n|LineColor       = #66DD22\n}}\n{{Episode list\n|EpisodeNumber   = 163\n|EpisodeNumber2  = 11\n|Title           = Being Gay and Religious\n|OriginalAirDate= {{Start date|2020|3|15}}\n|Viewers         = \n|ShortSummary    = Meri, Janelle, Christine, and Robyn go to Chicago to visit Mariah and her fianc\u00e9e, Audrey. Mariah discusses the difficulty of growing up gay in the polygamist church.\n|LineColor       = #66DD22\n}}\n{{Episode list\n|EpisodeNumber   = 164\n|EpisodeNumber2  = 12\n|Title           = Robyn vs. Kody\n|OriginalAirDate= {{Start date|2020|3|22}}\n|Viewers         = \n|ShortSummary    = Robyn's family has less than 30 days to move. Kody puts pressure on Robyn to buy a house while Robyn holds out hope that a rental will become available.\n|LineColor       = #66DD22\n}}\n{{Episode list\n|EpisodeNumber   = 165\n|EpisodeNumber2  = 13\n|Title           = The Heat Is On\n|OriginalAirDate= {{Start date|2020|3|29}}\n|Viewers         = \n|ShortSummary    = A forest fire forces Meri to evacuate. Time is running out for Robyn and her family to move. The birth of the second Brown grandchild is imminent. \n|LineColor       = #66DD22\n}}\n{{Episode list\n|